    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1063"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1063">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/3722.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Consul
                            <persName type="to">Johnson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consul Garrett telegraphs there are about one hundred Americans yet in Tampico
                    District at Columbus, Chamal and Osorio, also a number at Monterey and Saltillo,
                    cut off from communication. Would it be possible for you to reach them through
                    Constitutionalist territory? If possible to do so, you are authorized to employ
                    messengers if necessary. Department desires these Americans to leave Mexico as
                    soon as possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
